<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1208,2007]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1281,1307]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[284,465,1282,1308]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 20A, B, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[478,505,1282,1308]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">21</figureCitation>
A–F). Wingspan, 
<quantity box="[708,791,1282,1308]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
. Head vestiture dark bronze; scales of the vertex narrow, anteriorly directed (
<figureCitation box="[378,485,1318,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). Antenna dark brown with light brown annulets; scape whitish, orange and black, without pecten. Labial palpus very large, sickle-shaped, yellowish grey, with the outer suface of segment 2 dark brown proximally (
<figureCitation box="[370,474,1392,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21B</figureCitation>
). Body dark bronze dorsally (abdomen almost black), yellowish grey ventrally. Legs yellowish grey, outwards with dark brown areas (distally on femora; proximally on tibiae); tibial spurs dark brown on outer surface. Dorsal surface of forewing dark purplish brown with many yellowish, transverse short strigae (more numerous along costa), which tend to form longer lines below the middle and the extremity of the upper edge of the discal cell; fringe yellowish. Hind wing blackish grey, with its outer margin concave at the extremity of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1420,1428,1558,1572]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
; fringe greyish. Ventral surface of forewing dark brown, though yellowish along costa and inner margin. Ventral surface of hind wing dark brown; costa yellowish. Forewing venation (
<figureCitation box="[959,1106,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 21C, E</figureCitation>
): 
<collectionCode box="[1128,1147,1613,1639]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1146,1154,1631,1645]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">4</subScript>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1212,1231,1613,1639]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1230,1238,1631,1645]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">5</subScript>
merged together, forming a single vein that runs to the apex; base of 
<collectionCode box="[731,750,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[750,758,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
remote from 
<collectionCode box="[913,932,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[931,939,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
and separate from 
<collectionCode box="[1156,1175,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1175,1183,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
, which is stalked with 
<collectionCode box="[151,170,1687,1713]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[170,196,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">4+5</subScript>
; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[234,242,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
arising closer to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[456,464,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[576,584,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
; CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[651,659,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
free, arising closer to CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[957,965,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1078,1086,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
; CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1153,1161,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
strongly arched, coming very close to the distal section of CuP (
<figureCitation box="[588,690,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21E</figureCitation>
). Frenulum composed of four bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1229,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Hind wing venation (
<figureCitation box="[209,308,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21F</figureCitation>
): subcosta long, diverging from the upper edge of the cell from approximately the middle of the latter; Rs free, running to apex; Rs and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[547,555,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
separate, diverging distad; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[890,898,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
arched, arising closer to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1207,1215,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1332,1340,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
: M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1380,1388,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[204,212,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
connate; CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[377,385,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[496,504,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
fairly remote proximally. Abdominal segments (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1161,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
) without spinose zones; antero-abdominal sternum with short apodemes (that widen caudad) and weakly pigmented, rather short venulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1208,2007]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1436,151,250]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[199,390,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[404,551,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 20C, D</figureCitation>
): See also the line drawing given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P. E. L." box="[958,1100,1907,1933]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref24658" refString="Viette, P. E. L. (1986) Nouveaux Microlepidopteres de Madagascar (Oecophoridae et Gelechiidae) (New species of Malagasy Microlepidoptera-Oecophoridae and Gelechiidae). Bulletin mensuel de la Societe linneenne de Lyon, 55 (4), 109 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1986.10753" type="journal article" year="1986">Viette (1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1110,1192,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1735,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1415,750,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-160@18.[151,1436,736,1712]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 13. Torodora cameronella (Viette, [1957]), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, male genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 2761; D, aedeagus; E abdomen. Scale bar for the genitalia and aedeagus: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406486/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Corpus bursae elongate, not clearly delimited anteriorly. Ductus bursae as a mere extension of the corpus, distinctly swollen around the insertion of the ductus seminalis. Antrum present, rather small, tapering anteriorly. Ostium bursae in the membranous anteroventral region of segment 
<collectionCode box="[569,621,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">VIII</collectionCode>
. Apophyses anteriores tubular, though rather short; apophyses posteriores a bit more than twice as long as the former. Papillae anales separate, posteriorly acute in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
